Its a MOSFET based bridge, the Vgs potential needed to put the
FETs into full enhancement mode is 11.2v or thereabouts. At lower
voltages the FETs operate in their linear range (their Rds value
goes up) and they dissipate much more heat. (As Rds goes up, I2R
losses go up as well)

--Chuck


